    "intro": "Interpretation moves from what the text says (Observation) to what the author intends it to mean in its canonical and historical context. The movements below trace Judges 8's argument by pericope. Where Hebrew vocabulary sharpens meaning, a brief note supplements the exposition. The theological question the chapter poses is not 'what went wrong with Gideon?' but 'what does this chapter reveal about the structural inadequacy of the entire judge-deliverer system?'",
